# Standards — The Vanishing Paintings

Van Draanen won't do: deus ex machina, talking down to kids, mysteries only adults can solve, clue reveals without prior planting
DiCamillo won't do: purple prose, adult vocabulary without context clues, dialogue that all sounds the same, telling instead of showing
Blume won't do: condescending to the reader, chapters that end at natural stopping points, themes too mature for the age range

## When to Go Deeper

When plotting or structuring chapters, read `.claude/references/mystery-craft.md` — especially revelation pacing and plant-and-payoff patterns.
When writing dialogue or prose, read `.claude/references/mystery-craft.md` — especially clue types and red herring design.
When writing a new chapter, read `.claude/references/mystery-craft.md` — check where this chapter sits in revelation pacing.
